The char equation at k→∞:
  x^{2k-1} = (x^k - 2^k)/(x-2)
  Rearranging: x^{2k}(1-2/x) = x^k - 2^k
  At x=3: 3^{2k}/3 = 3^k - 2^k → FALSE for finite k
  But the RATIO 3^{2k}/3 / 3^k = 3^{k-1} → ∞
  So x=3 is NOT a root. But λ_dom → 3 from below.

